What I did in my app in that case is showing a single rationale for all requested permissions. It's simple but the caveat is you don't have the detail of which permissions has been revoked. So you can only display a message like "some critical permissions have been revoked, please go to the settings and fix that".

Here is a sample code of the method which is passed to the subscribe of `request`. I used a snackbar for the user feedback : 

``` java
private void onPermissionResult(Boolean granted) {
        if (granted) {
           // OK
            return;
        }
        // Test whether the user clicked on "never ask again",
        // adapt the action according to that.
        RxPermissions.getInstance(this)
                .shouldShowRequestPermissionRationale(this, CRITICAL_PERMISSIONS)
                .observeOn(AndroidSchedulers.mainThread())
                .subscribe(should -> {
                    SnackBar.Builder snack = new SnackBar.Builder(this)
                            .withMessageId(R.string.permission_required)
                            .withDuration(SnackBar.PERMANENT_SNACK)
                            .withStyle(SnackBar.Style.ALERT);
                    if (should) {
                        // "never ask again" not clicked, ask the user to retry the permission request.
                        snack.withActionMessageId(R.string.reask)
                                .withOnClickListener(token -> {
                                            // Ask again for permissions                                          
                                        }
                                );
                    } else {
                        // "never ask again" clicked, ask the user to fix that in the app settings.
                        snack
                                .withActionMessageId(R.string.settings)
                                .withOnClickListener(token -> {
                                            // Open the app settings
                                            AndroidUtils.startAppDetailsActivity(this);
                                        }
                                );
                    }
                    snack.show();
                });

    }
```

